Since $\mathbf{p}$ is the projection of $\mathbf{v}$ onto $\mathbf{w},$ $\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{p}$ is orthogonal to $\mathbf{w}.$  Hence,
\[\|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{p}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{p}\|^2 = \|\mathbf{v}\|^2.\]Since $\frac{\|\mathbf{p}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} = \frac{5}{7},$ $\|\mathbf{p}\| = \frac{5}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\|.$  Then
\[\|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{p}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{p}\|^2 = \|\mathbf{v}\|^2\]becomes
\[\left\| \mathbf{v} - \frac{5}{7} \mathbf{v} \right\|^2 + \left( \frac{5}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| \right)^2 = \|\mathbf{v}\|^2.\]Solving for $\|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{p}\|,$ we find
\[\|\mathbf{v} - \mathbf{p}\| = \frac{2 \sqrt{30}}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\|.\]Since $\mathbf{q}$ is the projection of $\mathbf{p}$ onto $\mathbf{v},$ $\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{q}$ is orthogonal to $\mathbf{v}.$  Hence,
\[\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{q}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{q}\|^2 = \|\mathbf{p}\|^2.\]Since $\mathbf{p}$ is the projection of $\mathbf{v}$ onto $\mathbf{w},$ $\|\mathbf{p}\| \le \|\mathbf{v}\|.$  Hence,
\[\|\mathbf{p} - \mathbf{q}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{q}\|^2 \le \|\mathbf{v}\|^2.\]Then
\[\left( \frac{5}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| - \|\mathbf{q}\| \right)^2 + \|\mathbf{q}\|^2 \le \|\mathbf{v}\|^2.\]Expanding, we get
\[\frac{24}{49} \|\mathbf{v}\|^2 - \frac{10}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| \|\mathbf{q}\| + \|\mathbf{q}\|^2 \le \|\mathbf{v}\|^2.\]Then
\[\|\mathbf{q}\|^2 - \frac{10}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| \|\mathbf{q}\| + \frac{24}{49} \|\mathbf{v}\|^2 \le 0.\]This factors as
\[\left( \|\mathbf{q}\| - \frac{12}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| \right) \left( \|\mathbf{q}\| - 2 \|\mathbf{v}\| \right) \le 0.\]Since $\|\mathbf{q}\| \ge 0,$ $\|\mathbf{q}\| \le \frac{12}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\|$ or $\|\mathbf{q}\| \le 2 \|\mathbf{v}\|.$  Hence, $\frac{\|\mathbf{q}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} \le \frac{12}{7}$ or $\frac{\|\mathbf{q}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} \le 2.$

If $\frac{\|\mathbf{q}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} \le \frac{12}{7},$ then $\|\mathbf{q}\| \le \frac{12}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| = \frac{12}{7} \cdot \frac{7}{5} \|\mathbf{p}\| = \frac{12}{5} \|\mathbf{p}\| = \frac{12}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| = \frac{12}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\|.$

If $\frac{\|\mathbf{q}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} \le 2,$ then $\|\mathbf{q}\| \le 2 \|\mathbf{v}\| = 2 \cdot \frac{7}{5} \|\mathbf{p}\| = \frac{14}{5} \|\mathbf{p}\| = \frac{14}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{7} \|\mathbf{v}\| = 2 \|\mathbf{p}\|.$

Therefore, $\frac{\|\mathbf{q}\|}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} \le \min \left( \frac{12}{7}, 2 \right) = \boxed{\frac{12}{7}}.$

